summary: I just re watched Ant Man and the Wasp and realised how much various plot details in the Avengers and related movies are similar...
body: I just re watched Ant Man and the Wasp and realised how much various plot details in the Avengers and related movies are similar to events in Big Hero 6, which was also a Marvel movie but pitched at a different audience. In Age of Ultron, Tony Stark had an Ai called Tadashi, who was one of the characters in Big Hero. So going on this, the various Avengers dong stuff in the Quantum zone is going to have repercussions.

Welcome to my personal blog.

→ My goal is to create a platform for awareness, visibility, and guidance for topics like chronic illness, mental illness, disability, trauma, and suicide. I also do Let's Plays, J-Pop translations, beauty vlogs, and more!

↑I now have a "tip jar!"↑

And a Patreon!

I live with fibromyalgia, narcolepsy, ulcerative colitis and other conditions that come along with them. I'm currently in recovery from living 20+ years with undiagnosed atlas subluxation complex and the resulting osteoarthritis (degenerative disc disease). Even with these challenges, I work as much as I can at multiple jobs (currently at 3, working on getting up to 4!) and my free time is used to work on content. Most of my paychecks go into caring for myself but I try to keep my schedule open for work. If I can't work enough, I can't afford my treatments or medications, and most of it isn't covered by insurance so it's out of pocket. If I can't take care of myself, I struggle at work, and I can't work on videos or resources either because my free time then needs to be devoted to recovery. It's kind of a vicious cycle but I strive to stick to a schedule that allows me to use my day off energy to creating content while still saving time for resting. ​ ​Your donations and patronage allow me to afford what I need to care for my body while still being able to follow my passions. Thank you so much for supporting my dreams.​

summary: I want MCU Ultron back. I know Vision is likely the only metal boy we’re getting back, but damn it. There was so much more to...
body:
I want MCU Ultron back. I know Vision is likely the only metal boy we’re getting back, but damn it. There was so much more to his movie and him as an intelligent being than being an expensive commercial for the next movies. I feel like his story shouldn’t be over. 

Tony ultimately, even if he didn’t know the details yet, made Ultron in anticipation for Thanos. But it went all wrong. Ultron was Tony’s hubris coming to life in a 9 foot tall vibranium shitbaby and everything in AOU led to CW which led to their defeat in IW. If they had been united as a team from the beginning, if the Accords hadn’t split them up, what would the fate of the universe have been instead? 

I just wanna find out that Ultron had a contingency plan for losing his last body and hid somewhere clever. Would be very interesting to learn that he hid inside Tony’s suits or something, transferred himself into the nanotech, has been close all along, nestled against his father’s heart, learning, observing the humans he so badly wanted to punish for his pain. 

And when Tony’s floating in space and scared, his metal son speaks to him, seemingly from beyond the grave. Tony thinks he’s officially having end of life hallucinations. He thinks of the astronauts who have been visited by angels and wants to laugh at his dying brain. But Ultron keeps talking. He’s been doing a lot of evolving since AOU. He gets it now. He can help. He can do what he was created to do. He can do it right this time.

Tony can correct what his sins brought upon his world, his family. Ultron can finally get some headpats from his pops and be a happy boy. If it has to be the real end for him this time, Vision will be there for his brother with a soft binary lullaby.

title: The Talk
body:
Avengers lounging around the common room. 
Suddenly Peter runs through, shedding his clothes while pulling on his Spiderman suit, "Fri, open the window!" and jumps out.
Steve, worried: "Is there trouble? Should we suit up and go after him?"
Clint, falling out of the vent, laughing his ass off: "Don't worry. Kid's just running from Stark."
Natasha, mommabear instincts awakening: "Why?"
Cling, still snickering: "Tony was trying to give him 'The Talk'."
